      <title>Accessing Remote Computing Clusters using Open-SSH</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/2025-03-18-using-ssh-remote-access/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 18 Mar 2025 12:24:46 +1100</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/2025-03-18-using-ssh-remote-access/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;general-guidelines&#34;&gt;General guidelines&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You basically have three entities you want to interlink and provide bidirectional access.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personal computer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remote computer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Github or Gitlab a/c server&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A copy of all my ssh keys is stored in &lt;code&gt;~/Dropbox/ssh-access-keys/&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;generate-ssh-key-pair&#34;&gt;Generate SSH Key Pair&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SSH public and private keys can be generated by:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-bash&#34; data-lang=&#34;bash&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;ssh-keygen -t ed25519
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;In the prompt for putting in the password, leave it blank and just press &amp;ldquo;Enter&amp;rdquo;, if ya don&amp;rsquo;t want to have a password-protected file.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
